I got the worst hair cut of my life at this place. No joke! I went here because the salon I normally go to wasn't open. The place was right next door, so I thought to myself "well, what's the worst that can happen? How bad can a haircut really get?" The answer to that question become eye-openingly apparent after I left.   As I looked over my hair in my car's mirror, I noticed that they gave me a bowl cut. I looked like Moe in the Three Stooges, perhaps even worse. There was nothing redeeming about it. I had two back-to-back business meetings right after and here I looked like a little twelve year old twerp. The situation bordered on absurdity.   The lady was snickering to herself as she gave me my haircut, so she was probably aware of how horrible it was and enjoying the moment sadistically.  When I went back to ask for a refund, she had the audacity to blame me for the haircut. Apparently I hadn't specified that I didn't want a bowl cut. I guess you have to bring a list of all of the styles of haircuts you don't want.   Maybe the place is good for five year old kids, but if you are an adult steer clear. I repeat, steer clear!

